parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electric power steering system can cause the loss of power assist, making it difficult or impossible to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The power steering warning message displays on the dashboard
the power steering assist is lost
the steering wheel becomes hard to turn
the vehicle is difficult to control
and the steering system may reset after turning off and restarting the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seatbelt cable can cause the seatbelt to detach or break, leaving the driver and passengers without proper restraint, which can lead to serious injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seatbelt cable breaks or detaches
the seatbelt cannot be secured
the seatbelt pulls out of its anchor point
the seatbelt shows signs of wear or damage.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Excessive Idle Power Drain by OnStar Module
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive idle power drain by the OnStar module can cause the car battery to drain rapidly, leading to battery death, even when the vehicle is not in use, leaving the driver stranded and potentially causing safety issues.
symptoms: The car battery dies or is drained rapidly
even when the vehicle is not in use
the vehicle is unable to start
the battery is consistently drained when the vehicle is not driven for an extended period.
